%3E%20that%20power%20core%20features%20behind%20these%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20lead%20a%20team%20of%2013%20other%20engineers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20doctorates%2C%20even%20though%20I%20don't%20have%20one%20myself.%20In%20my%20experience%2C%20it's%20more%20common%20to%20have%20a%20master's%20or%20Ph.D.%20than%20just%20a%20bachelor's%20in%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Ftech%2Fwhat-is-machine-learning%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20and%20machine%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%20field.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHere's%20how%20I%20got%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcareer-advice-google-ai-researcher-early-job-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20job%20at%20Google%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20a%20Ph.D.%20and%20how%20I%20stay%20up-to-date%20in%20this%20rapidly%20developing%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2264b15423-bd79-4976-893e-b76e1e77d446%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20thought%20about%20getting%20a%20Ph.D.%20but%20was%20offered%20a%20job%20at%20Google%20before%20I%20got%20the%20chance%20to%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20India%2C%20and%20for%20my%20bachelor's%2C%20I%20studied%20computer%20science%20at%20the%20Indian%20Institute%20of%20Technology%20Hyderabad.%20I'd%20always%20been%20interested%20in%20computers%2C%20so%20it%20felt%20natural%20to%20me%20to%20pursue%20this%20for%20my%20career.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwo%20years%20into%20my%20degree%2C%20I%20asked%20more%20senior%20peers%20at%20my%20university%20how%20I%20could%20make%20the%20most%20of%20my%20summer%20break.%20They%20suggested%20I%20find%20a%20research%20internship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20cold-emailed%2030%20to%2040%20professors%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20with%2C%20and%20finally%2C%20one%20academic%20at%20a%20university%20in%20Japan%20let%20me%20work%20on%20their%20research%20project.%20This%20got%20me%20into%20the%20AI%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-booming-is-phd-necessary-machine-learning-jobs-workers-2024-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emachine%20learning%3C%2Fa%3E%20world%20and%20the%20research%20mindset.%20The%20following%20summer%2C%20I%20did%20a%20different%20internship%2C%20also%20in%20machine%20learning.%20I%20wanted%20to%20go%20into%20machine%20learning%20because%20it%20was%20a%20rapidly%20developing%20field%20being%20used%20to%20solve%20hard%20problems%20like%20spam%20reduction.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20my%20research%20experience%20and%20high%20college%20grades%2C%20a%20Ph.D.%20felt%20like%20a%20natural%20future%20step%20for%20me.%20However%2C%20I%20became%20interested%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcodefights-thinks-competitive-programming-can-be-a-spectator-sport-2015-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecompetitive%20coding%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20a%20hobby%20during%20my%20degree%20too%2C%20and%20I%20became%20quite%20good%20at%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20participated%20in%20a%20coding%20competition%20organized%20by%20Google.%20The%20company%20noticed%20me%20and%20asked%20me%20to%20interview%20with%20them.%20It%20led%20to%20a%20job%20offer.%20My%20interviewer%20even%20offered%20me%20a%20job%20on%20his%20team%20because%20he%20really%20liked%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20going%20on%20to%20do%20a%20Ph.D.%20after%20graduating%20in%202015%2C%20I%20started%20working%20for%20Google%20in%20Bengaluru%20that%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2294c525e6-5858-4f8e-bcc6-3db2d3fde3cd%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ENow%2C%20I%20manage%20a%20team%20of%20other%20engineers%2C%20some%20of%20whom%20have%20Ph.D.s%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fex-google-manager-crafted-master-plan-to-get-promoted-quickly-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20manager%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20who%20interviewed%20me%2C%20briefly%20mentioned%20he%20liked%20my%20research%20internships%20and%20strong%20competitive%20coding%20background.%20He%20put%20me%20on%20a%20team%20working%20on%20an%20AI%20model%20for%20auto-capitalization%20in%20Google%20Docs.%20I%20also%20worked%20on%20improving%20the%20spellcheck.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202017%2C%20after%20being%20promoted%20to%20an%20L4%20engineer%2C%20I%20requested%20a%20move%20to%20the%20US%20with%20the%20company.%20Silicon%20Valley%20and%20computer%20science%20are%20synonymous%2C%20so%20working%20there%20was%20a%20dream%20for%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20move%2C%20I've%20been%20working%20on%20developing%20keyword-less%20ad%20technology.%20I%20built%20the%20first%20models%20for%20keyword-less%20targeting%20in%20PMax%2C%20and%20for%20my%20work%2C%20I%20received%20a%20Google%20Ads%20Tech%20Impact%20award.%20I%20also%20launched%20the%20final%20URL%20expansion%20and%20received%20another%20company%20award.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20moving%20to%20America%2C%20I've%20received%20two%20promotions%20and%20am%20now%20an%20engineering%20lead%20for%20a%20team%20of%2013.%20I'm%20responsible%20for%20choosing%20which%20projects%20my%20team%20works%20on%20to%20have%20a%20positive%20impact%20and%20help%20them%20progress%20in%20their%20careers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeveral%20people%20on%20my%20team%20have%20a%20master's%2C%20and%20multiple%20also%20have%20Ph.D.s.%20You%20can%20be%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgoogle-software-engineer-leetcode-coding-interview-prep-advice-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoogle%20engineer%3C%2Fa%3E%20without%20a%20master's%20or%20Ph.D.%2C%20but%20from%20what%20I've%20seen%2C%20most%20people%20in%20the%20AI%20and%20machine%20learning%20field%20have%20these%20qualifications%2C%20showing%20how%20competitive%20the%20field%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20first%20manager%20at%20Google%20gave%20me%20AI%20work%20without%20these%20qualifications%2C%20and%20while%20I%20don't%20know%20exactly%20why%2C%20I%20think%20having%20top%20grades%20in%20my%20bachelor's%20and%20two%20research%20internships%20helped.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20thrive%20and%20get%20promoted%20in%20AI%20without%20these%20qualifications%20because%20the%20field%20is%20changing%20rapidly.%20Your%20degree%20can%20give%20you%20a%20headstart%2C%20but%20to%20stay%20relevant%2C%20you%20need%20to%20regularly%20upskill.%20Without%20that%2C%20even%20a%20Ph.D.%20recipient%20can%20become%20irrelevant.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2214c66004-033f-4b9c-81e7-f9bd446d017e%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20make%20active%20efforts%20to%20stay%20competitive%20in%20my%20field%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EA%20couple%20of%20methods%20have%20particularly%20helped%20me%20stay%20up-to-date%20in%20my%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20is%20being%20part%20of%20a%20research%20paper%20reading%20group.%20Every%20two%20weeks%2C%20my%20team%20and%20I%2C%20and%20some%20other%20folks%20outside%20the%20team%2C%20meet.%20One%20person%20is%20tasked%20with%20reading%20a%20research%20paper%20in%20two%20weeks.%20At%20the%20meeting%2C%20they'll%20present%20the%20paper%20and%20talk%20about%20its%20new%20findings.%20The%20group%20critiques%20the%20paper%20and%20brainstorms%20whether%20we%20can%20use%20the%20research%20in%20our%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20found%20this%20is%20an%20efficient%20way%20to%20keep%20the%20team%20up-to-date.%20There%20are%20so%20many%20research%20papers%20out%20there%2C%20but%20this%20is%20a%20collective%20effort.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20thing%20is%20volunteering%20to%20review%20research%20papers.%20When%20new%20papers%20are%20developed%2C%20research%20conferences%20need%20people%20to%20volunteer%20their%20expertise%20and%20assess%20how%20novel%20they%20are.%20This%20means%20I%20can%20read%20papers%20before%20they're%20published%20and%20also%20give%20back%20to%20the%20research%20community.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI've%20been%20doing%20these%20two%20things%20for%20years.%20They've%20helped%20me%20develop%20my%20expertise%2C%20and%20I%20think%20they've%20played%20a%20part%20in%20helping%20me%20get%20promo