C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESukumar's%20screenplay%2C%20AA's%20crowd-pleasing%20mannerisms%20and%20Fahadh%20Faasil's%20extended%20presence%20(the%20widely%20admired%20Malayalam%20film%20actor%20embodies%20both%20levity%20and%20blustery%20bravado)%20unabashedly%20aimed%20at%20heightening%20the%20effect%20that%20the%20precursor%20had%20on%20audiences%20across%20the%20nation.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20effort%20yields%20mixed%20results.%20A%20couple%20of%20the%20film's%20set%20pieces%20-%20the%20principal%20ones%20are%20protracted%20and%20shrill%20affairs%20-%20work%20reasonably%20well.%20The%20rest%20do%20not.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECinematographer%20Miroslaw%20Kuba%20Brozek%2C%20whose%20exceptional%20skills%20shone%20through%20in%20the%20first%20film%20and%20contributed%20significantly%20to%20its%20impressive%20visual%20sweep%2C%20brings%20the%20same%20level%20of%20craftsmanship%20to%20bear%20upon%20the%20follow-up.%20That%20%3Cem%3EPushpa%20Part%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20no%20technical%20blemishes%20is%20par%20for%20the%20course%2C%20but%20its%20plot%20is%20disappointingly%20uneven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20couple%20of%20hours%20of%20the%20200-minute%20movie%20lurches%20from%20one%20flashpoint%20to%20another.%20Each%20brings%20out%20the%20import%20and%20scope%20of%20Pushpa's%20jhukega%20nahi%20rhetoric.%20His%20battle%20with%20IPS%20officer%20Bhanwar%20Singh%20Shekhawat%20(Faasil%2C%20who%2C%20unlike%20in%20Pushpa%3A%20The%20Rise%2C%20makes%20an%20appearance%20right%20at%20the%20outset%20here)%20hurtles%20towards%20what%20appears%20to%20be%20a%20culmination%20until%20the%20film%20throws%20up%20a%20surprise%20in%20its%20dying%20minutes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPushpa%20(Allu%20Arjun)%20is%20now%20a%20doting%20husband%20to%20Srivalli%20(Rashmika%20Mandanna)%20but%20he%20is%20anything%20but%20domesticated.%20His%20empire%20of%20crime%20is%20now%20wider%20than%20ever.%20He%20spreads%20his%20wings%20beyond%20the%20shores%20of%20India%20and%20swings%20a%20mammoth%20red%20sander%20deal%20with%20a%20Dubai-based%20buyer%20Hamid%20(Saurabh%20Sachdeva%20in%20a%20cameo).%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPushpa%20runs%20his%20gang%20with%20the%20help%20of%20his%20friend%20and%20trusted%20lieutenant%20Keshav%20(Jagadeesh%20Prathap%20Bandari)%20and%20is%20well%20served%20by%20a%20battalion%20of%20smugglers%20who%20never%20let%20the%20thought%20of%20betrayal%20cross%20their%20minds.%20However%2C%20as%20one%20would%20expect%20in%20movies%20like%20this%20one%2C%20Pushpa%20always%20fights%20the%20bad%20guys%20single-handedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20an%20axe-wielding%20criminal%20whose%20writ%20runs%20unchallenged%20in%20the%20forest%20that%20he%20lord%20over.%20His%20adversary%20is%20a%20corrupt%2C%20caricaturised%20cop.%20Pushpa%20is%20so%20secure%20in%20his%20saddle%20that%20he%20does%20no%20running%20at%20all.%20But%20the%20police%20officer%20charged%20with%20tearing%20down%20his%20illegal%20red%20sander%20business%20is%20constantly%20chasing%20shadows.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPushpa's%20grip%20on%20the%20smuggling%20syndicate%20is%20undisputed.%20He%20deals%20summarily%20with%20the%20threats%20that%20the%20police%20pose%20to%20his%20gang%2C%20leaving%20Shekhawat%2C%20the%20district's%20SP%2C%20fuming%20and%20at%20a%20loose%20end.%20The%20frustrated%20cop's%20desperate%20measures%20only%20aggravate%20matters%20between%20him%20and%20Pushpa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPushpa%20has%20to%20contend%20with%20another%20an%20equally%20persistent%20foe%2C%20Daksha%20(Anasuya%20Bharadwaj)%20and%20her%20smuggler-husband%20Mangalam%20Shrinu%20(Sunil).%20The%20woman%20exploits%20her%20proximity%20to%20SP%20Shekhawat%20to%20fish%20in%20troubled%20waters.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20indignity%20that%20Pushpa%20had%20subjected%20Shekhawat%20to%20in%20the%20past%2C%20he%20is%20forced%20to%20apologise%20to%20the%20man%20in%20uniform%20at%20a%20raucous%20party%20organised%20by%20a%20politician%20to%20broker%20a%20truce.%20But%20since%20he%20isn't%20the%20type%20to%20take%20a%20blow%20to%20his%20ego%20lying%20down%2C%20Pushpa%20settles%20scores%20before%20the%20party%20is%20over.%20The%20two%20men%20are%20back%20at%20each%20other's%20throat.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%20in%20the%20film%2C%20a%20thwarted%20photo%20op%20gets%20Pushpa's%20goat%20big%20time.%20He%20resolves%20to%20make%20the%20chief%20minister%20of%20the%20state%20pay%20a%20price%20for%20the%20effrontery.%20He%20throws%20his%20weight%20behind%20MLA%20Sidappa%20(Rao%20Ramesh).%20The%20repercussions%20of%20that%20political%20act%20take%20a%20while%20to%20manifest%20themselves%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20dearth%20of%20action%20in%20Pushpa's%20life%20in%20the%20interim%2C%20what%20with%20the%20police%20officer%20running%20around%20in%20circles%20in%20the%20hope%20of%20catching%20the%20smugglers%20red-handed.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20last%20one-third%20of%20the%20film%2C%20the%20plot%20veers%20off%20the%20main%20Pushpa-Shekhawat%20confrontation%20track%20-%20it%20is%20allowed%20to%20literally%20go%20up%20in%20flames%20-%20and%20settles%20on%20a%20personal%20angle%20that%20was%20alluded%20to%20several%20times%20in%20the%20first%20film%20-%20Pushpa's%20tense%20relationship%20with%20his%20half-brother%20Molleti%20Mohan%20Raj%20(Ajay)%2C%20who%20revels%20in%20humiliating%20the%20hero%20for%20being%20an%20illegitimate%20son.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohan's%20daughter%20Kaveri%20(Pavani%20Karanam)%20becomes%20a%20pawn%20in%20the%20hands%20of%20an%20adversary%20who%20surfaces%20late%20in%20the%20film%20and%20sets%20off%20a%20long%20climactic%20action%20sequence%20in%20which%20Pushpa%2C%20with%20his%20hands%20and%20legs%20tied%2C%20proves%20why%20he%20isn't%20just%20any%20odd%20fire%20anymore%2C%20but%20a%20veritable%20full-blown%20wildfire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EPushpa%3A%20The%20Rule%20-%20Part%202%3C%2Fem%3E%20kicks%20off%20with%20a%20nightmare%20that%20ends%20with%20the%20titular%20character%20plunging%20into%20a%20sea%20after%20being%20shot%20in%20the%20shoulder.%20He%20wakes%20up%20with%20a%20start%20and%20a%20suppressed%20shriek.%20His%20wife%20is%20alarmed%20although%20she%20is%20acutely%20aware%20that%20there%20is%20nothing%20in%20the%20world%20that%20can%20cow%20down%20Pushpa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20scene%20is%20followed%20by%20moments%20of%20awkward%20intimacy%20between%20AA%20and%20Rashmika%20-%20there%20are%20several%20more%20in%20the%20course%20of%20the%20film%20-%20that%20are%20clearly%20meant%20to%20be%20a%20response%20to%20criticism%20that%20Pushpa's%20exploits%20glorify%20violence%20and%20offensive%20masculinity%20(more%20on%20this%20aspect%20of%20the%20film%20later).%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20rest%20of%20%3Cem%3EPushpa%20Part%202%20%3C%2Fem%3Ehas%20the%20actor%20and%20the%20character%20in%20their%20elements%20all%20right.%20Allu%20Arjun%20is%20strikingly%20consistent.%20This%20is%20despite%20the%20fact%20that%20Pushpa's%20slanted%20shoulder%20does%20an%20inexplicable%20vanishing%20act%20after%20a%20point%20never%20to%20return%20although%20his%20personality-defining%20beard%20caresses%20are%20still%20very%20much%20part%20of%20the%20deal.%20However%2C%20the%20200-minute%20movie%20turns%20into%20a%20bit%20of%20an%20exhausting%20ordeal%20when%20it%20gropes%20in%20the%20dark%20for%20genuine%20inspiration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20women%20in%20Pushpa's%20life%20-%20his%20mother%20Parvathi%20(Kalpalatha)%20and%20his%20wife%20-%20are%20the%20only%20people%20who%20can%20bring%20him%20to%20his%20knees.%20Srivalli%20does%20just%20that%20after%20a%20tiff%20that%20allows%20the%20film%20to%20weave%20in%20a%20longish%20scene%20to%20assert%20Pushpa's%20non-sexist%20stance%20towards%20marital%20and%20other%20relationships.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20intrepid%20man%20goes%20androgynous%20with%20a%20vengeance%20in%20a%20song%20and%20dance%20sequence%20-%20a%20frenzied%20incantation%20performed%20by%20Pushpa%20to%20invoke%20the%20blessings%20of%20Goddess%20Kali.%20He%20wears%20a%20sari%20and%20his%20fearsomely%20piercing%20eyes%20are%20accentuated%20by%20kohl%20generously%20applied%20above%20his%20cheeks.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20full%20force%20of%20the%20fury%20of%20the%20fiery%20female%20divine%20is%20felt%20by%20a%20bunch%20of%20ruffians%20(they%20have%20glowing%20red%2C%20devilish%20horns%20on%20their%20heads)%20who%20barge%20into%20the%20religious%20ceremony%20asking%20for%20trouble.%20Pushpa%20gives%20it%20to%20them%2C%20with%20his%20avatar%20of%20the%20Goddess%20of%20Destruction%20unleashing%20a%20rampage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ciframe%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22strict-origin-when-cross-origin%5C%22%20allowfullscreen%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fembed%2F1kVK0MZlbI4%3Fsi%3DR057keVhKV9-PFC7%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22YouTube%20video%20player%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22315%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20self-same%20rampage%20is%20repeated%20in%20the%20climax.%20Pushpa%20once%20again%20dons%20the%20guise%20of%20Kali.%20After%20the%20hurly-burly%20is%20done%20and%20a%20wedding%20is%20underway%20to%20indicate%20an%20end%20to%20hostilities%2C%3Cem%3E%20Pushpa%20Part%202%20%3C%2Fem%3Epoints%20to%20a%20Part%203.%20The%20final%20chapter%20of%20the%20trilogy%20will%20be%20titled%20%3Cem%3EPushpa%3A%20The%20Rampage%3C%2Fem%3E.%20As%20if%20there%20hasn't%20been%20enough%20already.%20%C2%A0%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1733395680000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-12%2Fptive7cg_allu-arjun-_625x300_05_December_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fentertainment%2Fpushpa-the-rule-part-2-review-the-film-is-crushed-under-the-weight-of-its-own-vaulting-ambition-2-5-stars-7178499%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Pushpa%3A%20The%20Rule%20-%20Part%202%20Review%3A%20Allu%20Arjun%20is%20strikingly%20consistent%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%2