e%20mortars%2C%20shells%2C%20all%20connected%20to%20ammunition.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drone%20prototype%20with%20a%20rifle%20attached%20to%20its%20base%20sits%20on%20a%20field.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674d3d039e9761932b4a1e25%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChernyavskiy's%20drone%20rifle%20project%20hopes%20to%20create%20a%20flying%2C%20remote%20heavy%20rifle.%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20Chernyavskiy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ECrowdfunding%20has%20long%20been%20a%20pillar%20of%20Ukraine's%20war%20effort%2C%20with%20civilians%20pitching%20in%20for%20years%20to%20send%20aid%20supplies%2C%20clothing%2C%20and%20cash%20to%20the%20front%20lines.%20Low-cost%20drones%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drones-behind-80-russia-frontline-casualties-report-nyt-war-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproven%20to%20be%20effective%20on%20the%20modern%20battlefield%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20have%20become%20one%20of%20the%20hottest%20commodities%20among%20units%20battling%20Russian%20assaults.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20commonly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-drone-units-operate-like-edgy-tech-startups-military-russia-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrowdfunded%20drone%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20seven-inch%20commercial%20unit%20that%20carries%20a%20small%20payload%2C%20costs%20less%20than%20%241%2C000%20to%20build%20and%20arm.%20A%20typical%20155mm%20artillery%20shell%2C%20meanwhile%2C%20costs%20between%20%242%2C500%20and%20%244%2C000%20for%20Western%20factories%20to%20produce.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChernyavskiy%20said%20that%20drones%20can't%20replace%20artillery%2C%20which%20can%20suppress%20enemy%20forces%2C%20serve%20as%20fire%20support%2C%20and%20hammer%20front-line%20positions%20at%20range.%20But%20drones%20have%20their%20place%20in%20this%20war%2C%20as%20the%20world%20has%20repeatedly%20seen.%20With%20these%20systems%2C%20for%20around%20an%20average%20of%20%2415%2C000%2C%20his%20men%20can%20take%20out%20a%20Russian%20tank%20worth%20significantly%20more.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUkrainian%20fundraisers%20like%20him%20have%20formed%20a%20robust%20network%20that%20pulls%20in%20millions%20of%20dollars%20weekly%20for%20drones%2C%20working%20with%20a%20mix%20of%20local%20manufacturing%20lines%20to%20turn%20the%20cash%20into%20precision%20strike%20munitions.%20To%20keep%20donors%20abreast%20of%20their%20work%2C%20they%20report%20daily%20with%20first-person%20videos%20of%20exploding%20drones%20slamming%20into%20enemy%20positions%20and%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224022%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20worker%20builds%20a%20first-person%20view%20drone%20in%20Zaporizhzhia%2C%20southeastern%20Ukraine.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674d4ca6e45a68623a275a1a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222681%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDrones%20are%20often%20built%20in%20small%20workshops%20across%20Ukraine.%3Cp%3EDmytro%20Smolienko%20%2F%20Ukrinform%2FFuture%20Publishing%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EChernyavskiy%20said%20that%20Russian%20forces%20typically%20can't%20advance%20when%20harassed%20by%20drones.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20can%20have%20100%20explosions%20in%20one%20day%2C%20it%20means%20no%20Ukrainian%20will%20be%20killed%20this%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Swarming%20the%20air%20with%20recon%20drones%20also%20gives%20Moscow%20little%20chance%20to%20launch%20surprise%20attacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d6ee9162-4813-4cad-a2d2-0b5cf81ae78c%5C%22%3ECivilian%20war%20support%20at%20an%20'astonishing'%20scale%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20due%20to%20availability%2C%20there%20are%20days%20when%20his%20unit%20can%20only%20deploy%20five%2C%20maybe%2010%20drones%2C%20reducing%20resistance%20and%20allowing%20Russian%20troops%20to%20get%20close%20to%20Ukrainian%20trenches%20and%20overwhelm%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChernyavskiy%20said%20the%20flow%20of%20cash%20from%20civilian%20supporters%20is%20keeping%20his%20men%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20it's%20certainly%20unprecedented%2C%26quot%3B%20Federico%20Borsari%2C%20a%20resident%20fellow%20who%20studies%20technology%20and%20drone%20warfare%20at%20the%20Center%20for%20European%20Policy%20Analysis%20think%20tank%2C%20said%20of%20the%20current%20crowdfunding%20movement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBorsari%20said%20that%20drones%2C%20easy%20to%20build%20and%20deadly%2C%20have%20changed%20how%20civilians%20can%20support%20a%20war%20effort%20en%20masse.%20With%20Ukraine%2C%20an%20individual%20civilian%20can%20now%20remotely%20yet%20directly%20pay%20for%20a%20hit%20on%20an%20enemy%20soldier%20or%20tank%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReally%2C%20the%20scale%20of%20the%20rapport%20is%20astonishing%2C%26quot%3B%20Borsari%20said.%20%26quot%3BWe're%20talking%20about%20hundreds%20of%20thousands%20of%20drones%20provided%20to%20the%20Ukrainian%20military.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20Skarlat%2C%20a%20volunteer%20who%20has%20been%20running%20a%20fundraising%20Telegram%20channel%20since%20the%20war%20began%2C%20said%20most%20of%20his%20donors%20paying%20for%20drones%20are%20regular%20civilians%20sending%20part%20of%20their%20salaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOthers%20are%20small%20businesses%20with%20cash%20to%20spare%2C%20he%20said.%20Skarlat%2C%20a%20professional%20swimmer%2C%20works%20as%20a%20member%20of%20a%20Telegram%20network%20of%20five%20fundraising%20volunteers%20led%20by%20Ukrainian%20activist%20Serhii%20Sternenko.%20Skarlat%20told%20BI%20he's%20helped%20raise%20%242.5%20million%20for%20100%2C000%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftelegram.org%2Fjs%2Ftelegram-widget.js%3F22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20started%20using%20drones%20because%20of%20the%20lack%20of%20ammunition.%20It%20was%20from%20a%20need%20of%20striking%20positions%20and%20priority%20targets%20in%20the%20most%20effective%20and%20cheapest%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20Throughout%20the%20war%2C%20Ukraine%20has%20repeatedly%20struggled%20with%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraines-ammo-problems-hinder-ability-fire-at-russian-targets-2024-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einsufficient%20amounts%20of%20ammunition%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20such%20as%20much-need%20155mm%20artillery%20shells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Kyiv%2C%20restaurants%2C%20caf%C3%A9s%2C%20and%20barber%20shops%20often%20display%20QR%20codes%20for%20customers%20to%20throw%20in%20a%20few%20dollars%20for%20drone%20production%2C%20said%20Mark%20J.%20Lindquist%2C%20a%20former%20US%20Air%20Force%20analyst%20now%20living%20in%20Ukraine%20to%20crowdfund%20for%20local%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20has%20to%20be%20in%20the%20millions%2C%20if%20not%20tens%20or%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%2C%20because%20it's%20the%20most%20effective%20way%20for%20an%20average%20citizen%20to%20put%20together%20a%20small%20amount%20of%20money%20and%20make%20a%20huge%20difference%20on%20the%20battlefield%2C%26quot%3B%20Lindquist%20told%20BI.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELindquist%2C%20who%20worked%20as%20a%20motivational%20speaker%20before%20leaving%20for%20Ukraine%20in%202022%2C%20now%20flies%20back%20to%20the%20US%20regularly%20to%20raise%20money%20at%20public%20events%20for%20front-line%20units.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221600%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Mark%20Lindquist%20poses%20with%20a%20drone%20jammer%20and%20a%207-inch%20quadcopter%20drone.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674d3b8ae45a68623a2759b7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELindquist%20said%20he's%20personally%20helped%20raise%20funds%20for%20about%20300%20drones%20in%20Ukraine%20and%20organized%20other%20efforts%20for%201%2C000%20drones%20in%20total.%3Cp%3EMark%20Lindquist%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20estimates%20that%20he%20and%20his%20fundraising%20partners%20have%20brought%20in%20about%20%2413%20million%20in%20aid%2C%20and%20he%20now%20asks%20Americans%20to%20donate%20toward%20civilian%20vehicles%20and%20commercial%20drones%20that%20can%20be%20turned%20into%20weapons%20like%20loitering%20munitions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20Lindquist%20is%20frustrated%20with%20donors%20in%20the%20US%2C%20whom%20he%20says%20frequently%20balk%20at%20paying%20for%20something%20that%20can%20kill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BLargely%2C%20Americans%20have%20shied%20away%20from%20things%20that%20would%20drop%20these%20bombs%20you%20see%20on%20Instagram%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrones%20aren't%20always%20used%20for%20deadly%20ends%2C%20though.%20Chernyavskiy%20hopes%20to%20raise%20%2450%2C000%20to%20complete%20a%20land%20evacuation%20drone%20that%20can%20navigate%20deep%20forest%20terrain%20and%20retrieve%20lone%20Ukrainians%20guarding%20trenches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20land-based%20evacuation%20drone%20with%20tracks%20can%20be%20seen%20in%20a%20workshop.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674ea831e45a68623a2782ae%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChernyavskiy%20said%20his%20unit%20needs%20%2450%2C000%20to%20complete%20a%20land%20evacuation%20drone%20that%20can%20navigate%20rough%20terrain.%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20Chernyavskiy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20241st%20Territorial%20Brigade%20low%20on%20manpower%20and%20guns%2C%20Chernyavskiy%20said%20soldiers%20sometimes%20find%20themselves%20stationed%20alone%20on%20the%20front%20lines%20for%20abnormally%20long%20rotations.%20He%20said%20many%20fear%20it%20is%20a%20one-way%20ticket%20to%20the%20trenches.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20are%20injured%2C%20no%20one%20will%20help%20you%3B%20you%20have%20no%20chance%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BPeople%20usually%20spend%20one%20or%20two%20days%20in%20the%20trenches.%20Now%20they%20spend%20half%20a%20month.%20You%20can%20go%20crazy.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20drone%20that%20fetches%20the%20wounded%2C%20or%20even%20corpses%2C%20raises%20morale%20among%20troops%20who%20know%20that%20their%20bodies%20can%20still%20be%20returned%20to%20be%20honored%2C%20Chernyavskiy%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223fbc71f5-e82f-4326-975b-04ebec728901%5C%22%3EUS%20and%20European%20veterans%20fueling%20the%20crowdfunding%20effort%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EChernyavskiy's%20unit%20also%20receives%20cash%20from%20Americans%2C%20often%20from%20military%20veterans%20willing%20to%20chip%20in%20anything%20from%20lunch%20money%20to%20%2415%2C000%20each.%20He%20said%20he's%20brought%20about%20two%20dozen%20veterans%20to%20the%20front%20lines%20to%20see%20his%20unit's%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAfter%20they%20see%20what%20is%20going%20on%2C%20they%20help%20much%20faster%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20with%20a%20laugh.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Chernyavskiy%2C%20Lindquist%2C%20and%20a%20commander%20named%20Nikolay%20pose%20next%20to%20drones%20at%20a%20testing%20range.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674d41057929f317fb4f81f8%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChernyavskiy%2C%20pictured%20on%20the%20left%2C%20said%20he%20brought%20Lindquist%20to%20observe%20his%20unit's%20drone%20innovation%20work%20and%20is%20now%20working%20with%20him.%3Cp%3EOleksandr%20Chernyavskiy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20broad%20effort.%20Daniel%20Viksund%2C%20a%20Norwegian%20veteran%20who%20served%20two%20tours%20in%20Afghanistan%20as%20a%20combat%20engineer%20and%20tank%20driver%2C%20has%20been%20coordinating%20donations%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20primarily%20from%20Scandinavia%2C%20since%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20told%20BI%20that%20many%20of%20his%20donors%20are%20current%20and%20former%20military%20members%20who%2C%20after%20seeing%20videos%20of%20drones%20in%20action%2C%20sought%20to%20send%20more%20of%20them%20to%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BOur%20main%20focus%20is%20drones.%20Everybody%20was%20doing%20cars%20and%20medical%20stuff.%20Army%20veterans%20like%20us%2C%20we%20like%20to%20do%20things%20and%20make%20it%20happen%2C%26quot%3B%20Viksund%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHis%2020-man%20nonprofit%2C%20Veteran%20Aid%20Ukraine%2C%20has%20sent%20some%20500%20drones%20to%20Kyiv's%20forces%20and%20paid%20for%20about%202%2C500%20more.%20Viksund%20said%20videos%20sent%20to%20him%20from%20Ukrainian%20units%20show%20those%20drones%20have%20destroyed%20at%20least%2060%20main%20battle%20tanks%20and%20over%20100%20armored%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Three%20boxes%20filled%20with%20FPV%20drones%20are%20seen%20in%20the%20picture%20on%20the%20left%2C%20while%20Viksund%20poses%20in%20front%20of%20a%20tank%20in%20a%20picture%20on%20the%20right.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674d4fbe7929f317fb4f824f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EViksund%20has%20been%20supplying%20drones%20to%20Ukrainian%20units%20since%202022.%3Cp%3EDaniel%20Viksund%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EHe's%20proud%20of%20his%20organization's%20work%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fukraine-could-lose-crucial-town-chasiv-yar-donsetsk-intel-official-2024-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EChasiv%20Yar%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20they%20sent%20200%20drones%20to%20units%20defending%20the%20embattled%20city%20in%20late%20spring%20as%20US%20congressional%20infighting%20locked%20up%20billions%20in%20vital%20aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EViksund%20said%20Veteran%20Aid%20Ukraine%20alone%20can't%20provide%20nearly%20enough%20drones%20for%20Kyiv's%20remote%20operators.%20He%20estimates%20that%20they%20expend%204%2C000%20drones%20on%20average%20a%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBut%20when%20all%20the%20small%20rivers%20come%20together%2C%20you%20make%20a%20big%20river%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERussian%20organizations%20have%20also%20been%20donating%20drones%20for%20Moscow's%20units%2C%20but%20not%20on%20such%20a%20scale.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20necessarily%20see%20the%20same%20level%20of%20grassroots%20efforts%20in%20Russia%20because%20they%20have%20the%20state%20capacity%20and%20state%20resources%20to%20marshal%20the%20economy%20toward%20the%20war%20in%20a%20different%20way%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jennifer%20Kavanagh%2C%20director%20of%20military%20analysis%20at%20the%20think%20tank%20Defense%20Priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKavanagh%20said%20the%20crowdfunding%20effort%20has%20been%20meaningful%20in%20filling%20gaps%20in%20Western%20aid%2C%20though%20it's%20dwarfed%20by%20the%20sheer%20might%20of%20the%20traditional%20arsenals%20sent%20to%20Kyiv.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20and%20Europe%20have%20collectively%20sent%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ifw-kiel.de%2Ftopics%2Fwar-against-ukraine%2Fukraine-support-tracker%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%2490%20billion%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20military%20aid%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20powerful%20F-16%20fighter%20jets%2C%20long-range%20missile%20platforms%2C%20and%20millions%20of%20ammunition%20rounds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2286e0399f-092a-47ad-9f82-2310f76915c8%5C%22%3EReturn%20on%20investment%20in%20war%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20Western%20donors%20and%20volunteers%20say%20that%20lower-tech%20drones%20can%20make%20a%20significant%20difference%20for%20just%20a%20fraction%20of%20that%20cost.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20donor%20is%20a%20wealthy%20software%20engineer%20in%20the%20US%20Mountain%20West%20who%20said%20that%20he%20had%20spent%20about%20%24105%2C000%20sending%20142%20drones%20to%20Ukraine%2C%20including%20eight%20Chinese-made%20Mavics%20that%20cost%20around%20%241%2C700%20each%20and%20are%20popular%20for%20recon%20missions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20six%20kids%20at%20home%2C%20he%20told%20BI%20that%20he's%20cut%20back%20on%20purchases%20like%20upgrading%20their%202011%20GMC%20Savannah%20and%20fixing%20his%20couch.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20just%20think%20that%20if%20I%20spend%20a%20little%20less%2C%20someone%20will%20survive.%20Someone%20will%20have%20a%20husband%20and%20father%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20software%20engineer%2C%20who%20asked%20not%20to%20be%20named%20out%20of%20concern%20that%20Russian%20intelligence%20services%20would%20target%20him.%20BI%20knows%20his%20identity%20and%20has%20verified%20his%20donations%20to%20a%20Ukrainian%20platform.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20his%20favorite%20items%20is%20a%2010-inch%20drone%20made%20from%20DJI%20parts%20that%20can%20be%20converted%20into%20a%20bomber%20with%20a%20six-pound%20payload.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20each%20of%20these%20%241%2C600%20drones%20has%20a%20typical%20lifespan%20of%2050%20missions%20and%20that%2C%20with%20a%20minimum%20hit%20rate%20of%2033%25%2C%20delivers%20at%20least%2016%20strikes%20on%20Russian%20targets.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20give%20these%20guys%20%24100%20million%2C%20they%20can%20win%20the%20war%20for%20you%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20A%20common%20hope%20among%20drone%20warfare%20enthusiasts%20is%20that%20with%20more%20drones%20and%20jammers%2C%20Ukraine%20can%20effectively%20slow%20the%20Russian%20advance%20while%20exhausting%20its%20manpower%20and%20equipment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20drone%20operator%20of%20the%2015th%20Brigade%20flies%20a%20drone%20used%20as%20a%20loitering%20munition%20in%20a%20wheat%20field.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F674d493be45a68623a275a0a%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%2